'''Abe no Yoshimasa''' (安倍 吉昌) was a mid-[[Heian period]] aristocrat, [[:en:Onmyōji|Onmyōji]], and practitioner of [[:en:Onmyōdō|Onmyōdō]]. He was the second son of [[:en:Abe no Seimei|Abe no Seimei]] (according to some accounts) and held positions such as {{ill|Tenmon Hakase|ja|天文博士|1=Tenmon Hakase|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tenmon Hakase|13=User:Immanuelle/Tenmon Hakase|qq=}} (Doctor of Astronomy), {{ill|Onmyō Hakase|ja|陰陽博士|1=Onmyō Hakase|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Onmyō Hakase|13=User:Immanuelle/Onmyō Hakase|qq=}}, {{ill|Shukeitō|ja|主計頭|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shukeitō|qq=}}, and {{ill|Onmyō no Kami|ja|陰陽頭|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Onmyō no Kami|qq=}}. He was granted the Rank of ''Jushiijo'' (従四位上). Alongside his elder brother, {{ill|Abe no Yoshihira|ja|安倍吉平|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Abe no Yoshihira|qq=}}, and other prominent Onmyōji such as {{ill|Kamo clan|ja|賀茂朝臣氏|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kamo clan|qq=}}, he played a central role in leading the {{ill|Onmyōryō|ja|陰陽寮|1=Yin-Yang Bureau|2=ja|3=陰陽寮|4=fr|5=Bureau d'Onmyō|6=zh|7=阴阳寮|8=ko|9=음양료|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Onmyōryō|13=User:Immanuelle/Yin-Yang Bureau|qq=}} and the field of Onmyōdō.
